lawt.engine

Class Entity

  • java.lang.Object
    • lawt.engine.Entity

  • public abstract class Entity
extends java.lang.Object
    An Entity represents some object that can be drawn and manipulated in some window.
    An instance of Entity can be manipulated like a physical object via acceleration, friction, position, etc...

    Entity is intended to be extended, and methods for drawing/updating should be implemented.

    Author:
    Lucas
    See Also:
    Window

      • getEdgeBehavior

        public Entity.EdgeBehavior getEdgeBehavior()
        Gets the current edge behavior for this Entity

        CLAMP - Borders act as walls keeping Entity in Window
        WRAP - Entity will be moved to opposite side of Window when border is crossed
        NONE - Entity can pass borders, and leave visible window

        Returns:
        Current edge behavior in use

      • setEdgeBehavior

        public void setEdgeBehavior(Entity.EdgeBehavior edgeBehavior)
        Set edge behavior for this Entity to follow

        CLAMP - Borders act as walls keeping Entity in Window
        WRAP - Entity will be moved to opposite side of Window when border is crossed
        NONE - Entity can pass borders, and leave visible window

        Parameters:
        edgeBehavior - edge behavior to specify
